Name: Unearthed Treasure (Common)
Description:
Approximately (200 - 500) years old.

Dusty and mudstained, this treasure is nonetheless an important historical artifact.

Name: Unearthed Treasure (Uncommon)
Description:
Approximately (600 - 1100) years old.

Valuable in and of itself, this artifact is made priceless by the glimpse it gives into the society that once ruled this planet.

Name: Unearthed Treasure (Rare)
Description:
Approximately (1400 - 3000) years old.

This rare treasure is covered in strange markings, as if the contents were used in some sort of rite or ritual.

Name: Historical Document (Common)
Description:
Approximately (200 - 500) years old.

The paper is crumbling, the ink is fading. This may be the final opportunity anyone has to read this manuscript before time claims it for good.

Name: Historical Document (Uncommon)
Description:
Approximately (600 - 1100) years old.

Several of these pages appear stained, though there have been some clumsy attempts to clean them, and the second half has clearly been written in a different hand to the first...

Name: Historical Document (Rare)
Description:
Approximately (1400 - 3000) years old.

This manuscript is beautifully illustrated, with flowing calligraphy and dramatic, gilded illuminations. It is a work of exceptional artistry.

Name: Biological Sample (Common)
Description:
Approximately (200 - 500) years old.

There is a curious, sour aroma emanating from this sample. It is almost as if it has been slowly fermenting.

Name: Biological Sample (Uncommon)
Description:
Approximately (600 - 1100) years old.

This sample looks unnaturally clean, as if all other life that came into contact with it has been burned away.

Name: Biological Sample (Rare)
Description:
Approximately (1400 - 3000) years old.

This sample is still biologically active. It is releasing small puffs of gas on a remarkably regular cycle. The odour appears to change with each emission.

Name: Fossil Sample (Common)
Description:
Approximately (200 - 500) years old.

A well-preserved find, this fossil gives a glimpse of the strange creatures that used to roam this world.

Name: Fossil Sample (Uncommon)
Description:
Approximately (600 - 1100) years old.

Time has polished this fossil, giving it a pearlescent sheen, its surfacing shimmering in the light.

Name: Fossil Sample (Rare)
Description:
Approximately (1400 - 3000) years old.

The remains of a truly strange being. This fragment, dead and decayed, offers only the merest glimpse of what must have been a magnificent sight in life.

Name: Delicate Flora (Common)
Description:
Approximately (200 - 500) years old.

A relatively common plant, suffering from a relatively uncommon mutation. Spores of this size are not normal.

Name: Delicate Flora (Uncommon)
Description:
Approximately (600 - 1100) years old.

This plant has remarkably poisonous leaves, highly toxic petals, and release a scent that causes mild intoxication. Handle with care.

Name: Delicate Flora (Rare)
Description:
Approximately (1400 - 3000) years old.

A spectacular plant, once thought entirely extinct. It blooms rarely, and its precious flowers have inspired poetry, music and occasional murders.

Name: Lost Artifact (Common)
Description:
Approximately (200 - 500) years old.

Past its prime long before it was entombed, this tool was well-loved during its useful life. A family memento, perhaps, or a novice's training instrument?

Name: Lost Artifact (Uncommon)
Description:
Approximately (600 - 1100) years old.

Buried alongside its schematic, this remarkable tool was perhaps an original prototype. More than just an object, this find represents the inventive drive in a raw and early form.

Name: Lost Artifact (Rare)
Description:
Approximately (1400 - 3000) years old.

Buried with great care, this tool shows little sign of use. Perhaps it was an offering, made especially to be locked away from the physical world, its pristine nature emphasising how much this gesture meant to the burier.

Name: Aquatic Treasure (Common)
Description:
A well-preserved marine treasure, found deep under the ocean. It was protected from the elements by a thick sea-chest, and is at least (2 - 5)00 years old.

Highly valuable to collectors of ancient artifacts.

Name: Aquatic Treasure (Uncommon)
Description:
A well-preserved marine treasure, found deep under the ocean. It was protected from the elements by a thick sea-chest, and is at least (6 - 11)00 years old.

Highly valuable to collectors of ancient artifacts.

Name: Aquatic Treasure (Rare)
Description:
A well-preserved marine treasure, found deep under the ocean. It was protected from the elements by a thick sea-chest, and is at least (14 - 30)00 years old.

Highly valuable to collectors of ancient artifacts.

Name: Terrifying Sample (Common)
Description:
An appalling relic, the haunted remains of some abyssal horror. It has lived at least (2 - 5)0 lifetimes, and will live many more again.

Will stalk the bearer across the galaxy and the next, unless it is sold before the curse can take effect.

Name: Terrifying Sample (Uncommon)
Description:
An appalling relic, the haunted remains of some abyssal horror. It has lived at least (6 - 11)0 lifetimes, and will live many more again.

Will stalk the bearer across the galaxy and the next, unless it is sold before the curse can take effect.

Name: Terrifying Sample (Rare)
Description:
An appalling relic, the haunted remains of some abyssal horror. It has lived at least (14 - 30)0 lifetimes, and will live many more again.

Will stalk the bearer across the galaxy and the next, unless it is sold before the curse can take effect.

Name: Salvaged Scrap (Common)
Description:
Approximately (200 - 500) years old.

A reliable and common design, this technology was at the heart of Gek starship construction for years. Its ubiquity ensured a long life, as it was often recycled into countless other machines. It was particularly common as a repurposed Exocraft repair module.

Name: Salvaged Scrap (Uncommon)
Description:
Approximately (600 - 1100) years old.

A classic example of Korvax engineering, this technological component is solidly manufactured and has endured the passage of time well.

Name: Salvaged Scrap (Rare)
Description:
Approximately (1400 - 3000) years old.

Only an expert could determine the original purpose of this enigmatic technology. It vibrates gently, and certain species of creature seem to take great care to avoid it.

Name: Excavated Bones (Common)
Description:
Approximately (250 - 500) years old.

A motley assortment of bones from a long-extinct creature. Tell-tale pitting on this sample points to it having been consumed, digested, and expelled by some larger predator.

Name: Excavated Bones (Uncommon)
Description:
Approximately (600 - 1100) years old.

This complete set of vertebrae from a multi-headed creature raises more questions than it answers. A curious find.

Name: Excavated Bones (Rare)
Description:
Approximately (1400 - 3000) years old.

This intact skeleton was found buried with another, tragically smaller, variation of the same form. It is impossible to tell whether the adult creature or its young perished first.

Name: Ancient Skeleton (Common)
Description:
Approximately <VAL_ON>(250 - 500)00<> years old, and made from pure gold.

These bones are unlike those of any terrestial creature. The remains of a true deep-space leviathan.

Name: Ancient Skeleton (Uncommon)
Description:
Approximately <VAL_ON>(600 - 1100)00<> years old, and made from pure gold.

These bones are unlike those of any terrestial creature. The remains of a true deep-space leviathan.

Name: Ancient Skeleton (Rare)
Description:
Approximately <VAL_ON>(1400 - 3000)00<> years old, and made from pure gold.

These bones are unlike those of any terrestial creature. The remains of a true deep-space leviathan.

Name: Mainframe Access Card (Common)
Description:
<STELLAR>%OFFICER%<>'s security pass from the <TECHNOLOGY>%FREIGHTER%<>. It is warped and pockmarked, its surface melted by some unknown substance.

Records indicate it was last used %DAYS% days ago.

Name: Mainframe Access Card (Uncommon)
Description:
<STELLAR>%OFFICER%<>'s security pass from the <TECHNOLOGY>%FREIGHTER%<>. A rusty, dark red substance has congealed across its surface.

Records indicate it was last used %DAYS% days ago.

Name: Mainframe Access Card (Rare)
Description:
<STELLAR>%OFFICER%<>'s security pass from the <TECHNOLOGY>%FREIGHTER%<>. The pass is unnervingly pristine, almost as if coated in a substance that repels all other material.

Records indicate it was last used %DAYS% days ago.

Description: A scrap of organic matter. It is not clear if this is a lifeform in its own right, or some ejected/severed part of a larger being. Unlikely to be desirable at a galactic exchange. Select in the Inventory (INVENTORY<>) and use FE_ALT1<> to process it into useful materials.

Description: A damaged technology component, ejected from its machine and discarded by its owner. Worthless, except as scrap. Select in the Inventory (INVENTORY<>) and use FE_ALT1<> to break it down into useful materials.
